title: Google\Cloud\Container\V1\Cluster
name: Cluster
description:
A Google Kubernetes Engine cluster.

Generated from protobuf message google.container.v1.Cluster

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The name of this cluster. The name must be unique within this project and location (e.g. zone or region), and can be up to 40 characters with the following restrictions: Lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens only. Must start with a letter. * Must end with a number or a letter.

params.name: data.description
params.description: An optional description of this cluster.

params.name: data.initial_node_count
params.description: The number of nodes to create in this cluster. You must ensure that your Compute Engine resource quota is sufficient for this number of instances. You must also have available firewall and routes quota. For requests, this field should only be used in lieu of a "node_pool" object, since this configuration (along with the "node_config") will be used to create a "NodePool" object with an auto-generated name. Do not use this and a node_pool at the same time. This field is deprecated, use node_pool.initial_node_count instead.

params.name: data.node_config
params.description: Parameters used in creating the cluster's nodes. For requests, this field should only be used in lieu of a "node_pool" object, since this configuration (along with the "initial_node_count") will be used to create a "NodePool" object with an auto-generated name. Do not use this and a node_pool at the same time. For responses, this field will be populated with the node configuration of the first node pool. (For configuration of each node pool, see node_pool.config) If unspecified, the defaults are used. This field is deprecated, use node_pool.config instead.

params.name: data.master_auth
params.description: The authentication information for accessing the master endpoint. If unspecified, the defaults are used: For clusters before v1.12, if master_auth is unspecified, username will be set to "admin", a random password will be generated, and a client certificate will be issued.

params.name: data.logging_service
params.description: The logging service the cluster should use to write logs. Currently available options: "logging.googleapis.com/kubernetes" - the Google Cloud Logging service with Kubernetes-native resource model logging.googleapis.com - the Google Cloud Logging service. none - no logs will be exported from the cluster. if left as an empty string,logging.googleapis.com will be used.

params.name: data.monitoring_service
params.description: The monitoring service the cluster should use to write metrics. Currently available options: monitoring.googleapis.com - the Google Cloud Monitoring service. none - no metrics will be exported from the cluster. * if left as an empty string, monitoring.googleapis.com will be used.

params.name: data.network
params.description: The name of the Google Compute Engine network to which the cluster is connected. If left unspecified, the default network will be used.

params.name: data.cluster_ipv4_cidr
params.description: The IP address range of the container pods in this cluster, in CIDR notation (e.g. 10.96.0.0/14). Leave blank to have one automatically chosen or specify a /14 block in 10.0.0.0/8.

params.name: data.addons_config
params.description: Configurations for the various addons available to run in the cluster.

params.name: data.subnetwork
params.description: The name of the Google Compute Engine subnetwork to which the cluster is connected.

params.name: data.node_pools
params.description: The node pools associated with this cluster. This field should not be set if "node_config" or "initial_node_count" are specified.

params.name: data.locations
params.description: The list of Google Compute Engine zones in which the cluster's nodes should be located.

params.name: data.enable_kubernetes_alpha
params.description: Kubernetes alpha features are enabled on this cluster. This includes alpha API groups (e.g. v1alpha1) and features that may not be production ready in the kubernetes version of the master and nodes. The cluster has no SLA for uptime and master/node upgrades are disabled. Alpha enabled clusters are automatically deleted thirty days after creation.

params.name: data.resource_labels
params.description: The resource labels for the cluster to use to annotate any related Google Compute Engine resources.

params.name: data.label_fingerprint
params.description: The fingerprint of the set of labels for this cluster.

params.name: data.legacy_abac
params.description: Configuration for the legacy ABAC authorization mode.

params.name: data.network_policy
params.description: Configuration options for the NetworkPolicy feature.

params.name: data.ip_allocation_policy
params.description: Configuration for cluster IP allocation.

params.name: data.master_authorized_networks_config
params.description: The configuration options for master authorized networks feature.

params.name: data.maintenance_policy
params.description: Configure the maintenance policy for this cluster.

params.name: data.binary_authorization
params.description: Configuration for Binary Authorization.

params.name: data.autoscaling
params.description: Cluster-level autoscaling configuration.

params.name: data.network_config
params.description: Configuration for cluster networking.

params.name: data.default_max_pods_constraint
params.description: The default constraint on the maximum number of pods that can be run simultaneously on a node in the node pool of this cluster. Only honored if cluster created with IP Alias support.

params.name: data.resource_usage_export_config
params.description: Configuration for exporting resource usages. Resource usage export is disabled when this config is unspecified.

params.name: data.authenticator_groups_config
params.description: Configuration controlling RBAC group membership information.

params.name: data.private_cluster_config
params.description: Configuration for private cluster.

params.name: data.database_encryption
params.description: Configuration of etcd encryption.

params.name: data.vertical_pod_autoscaling
params.description: Cluster-level Vertical Pod Autoscaling configuration.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output only] Server-defined URL for the resource.

params.name: data.zone
params.description: [Output only] The name of the Google Compute Engine zone in which the cluster resides. This field is deprecated, use location instead.

params.name: data.endpoint
params.description: [Output only] The IP address of this cluster's master endpoint. The endpoint can be accessed from the internet at https://username:password@endpoint/. See the masterAuth property of this resource for username and password information.

params.name: data.initial_cluster_version
params.description: The initial Kubernetes version for this cluster. Valid versions are those found in validMasterVersions returned by getServerConfig. The version can be upgraded over time; such upgrades are reflected in currentMasterVersion and currentNodeVersion. Users may specify either explicit versions offered by Kubernetes Engine or version aliases, which have the following behavior: - "latest": picks the highest valid Kubernetes version - "1.X": picks the highest valid patch+gke.N patch in the 1.X version - "1.X.Y": picks the highest valid gke.N patch in the 1.X.Y version - "1.X.Y-gke.N": picks an explicit Kubernetes version - "","-": picks the default Kubernetes version

params.name: data.current_master_version
params.description: [Output only] The current software version of the master endpoint.

params.name: data.current_node_version
params.description: [Output only] Deprecated, use NodePools.version instead. The current version of the node software components. If they are currently at multiple versions because they're in the process of being upgraded, this reflects the minimum version of all nodes.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: [Output only] The time the cluster was created, in RFC3339 text format.

params.name: data.status
params.description: [Output only] The current status of this cluster.

params.name: data.status_message
params.description: [Output only] Additional information about the current status of this cluster, if available.

params.name: data.node_ipv4_cidr_size
params.description: [Output only] The size of the address space on each node for hosting containers. This is provisioned from within the container_ipv4_cidr range. This field will only be set when cluster is in route-based network mode.

params.name: data.services_ipv4_cidr
params.description: [Output only] The IP address range of the Kubernetes services in this cluster, in CIDR notation (e.g. 1.2.3.4/29). Service addresses are typically put in the last /16 from the container CIDR.

params.name: data.instance_group_urls
params.description: Deprecated. Use node_pools.instance_group_urls.

params.name: data.current_node_count
params.description: [Output only] The number of nodes currently in the cluster. Deprecated. Call Kubernetes API directly to retrieve node information.

params.name: data.expire_time
params.description: [Output only] The time the cluster will be automatically deleted in RFC3339 text format.

params.name: data.location
params.description: [Output only] The name of the Google Compute Engine zone or region in which the cluster resides.

params.name: data.enable_tpu
params.description: Enable the ability to use Cloud TPUs in this cluster.

params.name: data.tpu_ipv4_cidr_block
params.description: [Output only] The IP address range of the Cloud TPUs in this cluster, in CIDR notation (e.g. 1.2.3.4/29).

params.name: data.conditions
params.description: Which conditions caused the current cluster state.

methods.name: getInitialClusterVersion
methods.description:
The initial Kubernetes version for this cluster. Valid versions are those found in validMasterVersions returned by getServerConfig. The version can be upgraded over time; such upgrades are reflected in currentMasterVersion and currentNodeVersion.

Users may specify either explicit versions offered by Kubernetes Engine or version aliases, which have the following behavior:

  • "latest": picks the highest valid Kubernetes version
  • "1.X": picks the highest valid patch+gke.N patch in the 1.X version
  • "1.X.Y": picks the highest valid gke.N patch in the 1.X.Y version
  • "1.X.Y-gke.N": picks an explicit Kubernetes version
  • "","-": picks the default Kubernetes version

Generated from protobuf field string initial_cluster_version = 103;
